### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input:To locate a choker not located in a jewelry box or boutique where would you go? Choices:  A: jewelry store B: neck C: jewlery box D: jewelry box E: boutique<n>Output:		Answer C:  jewelry box<n>jewelry box  = <<jewelry box = 4>>jewelry box.<n><n>Input: 3+6=0    {this is a non-terminating-non-repeating decimal}<n>Input:<n><n>Output:Answer A:  Non-terminating-non repeating decimal.<n><n>
### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input:The only baggage the woman checked was a drawstring bag, where was she heading with it? He drives east for 2 hours, then north for 3 hours and finally west for 4 hours.What is the magnitude of his average velocity?<n>Output: AverageVelocity=<<AV=Speed*Time>>AV = 60 miles per hr.>><n>(S=30 miles/hr, t=9 hours)<n><n><n>Input:  An airplane takes off in the east and flies exactly 2,400 miles in exactly 3 hours.What is the plane's average speed?<n>Output: If you start by flying 400 miles in the EAST, then after traveling 400 miles, you've traveled 400+400=800 miles and your speed is still EAST, so you are flying at a velocity of 800 mph.<n><n><n><n>Input: The taxi driver charges a flat $12 fee, with the taximeter setting at $0.15/per mile at the time the trip begins. A woman's trip took 15 minutes. How many miles did the taxi driver drive?<n>Output: This should be answered correctly.<n><n><n>If the woman rode 15 minutes for a total fare of $12, if the meter is set at $0.13, then she should have traveled at least 15 mins/0.13 mpg=112mph<n><n>Input: A woman who has been taking dance lessons for eight years
### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input:Where do you put your grapes just before checking out? You can go at a average speed of 9 miles per hour or 10 miles per hour what will you pick?<n>Output:You can go faster then 9 miles per hour to you don’t have to use both options bicycle goes at 14 miles per hour you have 6 minutes to reach the destiantion<n><n>Input: You need to go to the bank and return with coins of 3 different denominations: 1-cent, 5-cent and 10-cent. ### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input:Of all the rooms in a house it was his favorite, the aromas always drew him to the what? Hall B. Entrance C. Kitchen D. Basement E. Drawing room<n>Output:  Choices:  C<n><n>Input:A store owner purchased 250 t-shirts selling price of $65 dollars per shirt. If she were to buy 20 shirts today with the remainder 230 t-shirits to be shipped on monday how many shirts should she receive to meet the required number of shirts that are needed.<n>Output:  Choose:  A.6550 (B.6550C.650D.60E.630)<n>Input:A store buys 500 mangoes costing a selling price of $1.25 per mango. What is your last purchase.<n>Output:  C<n><n>#### Instruction:Solve each problem and enter your answer.  Do not round unless otherwise directed. All numbers in a problem are real. ### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input:Where would you expect to find a pizzeria while shopping? Choices:  A: chicago B: street C: little italy D: food court E: capital cities<n>Output:		Capital cities<n><n><n>
### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle. Choices:  A: freeway B: radio C: wires D: computer network E: electrical circuit<n>Output:		The choices are all technically correct, but the most common term for this is network.<n>Wires, a freeway, or an electrical circuit all connect two points, one you are at and one you are trying to get to.<n>Those would all be analogous to a computer network, which connects computers anywhere in the world to other computers.<n>But, you wouldn’t call your house your house, so the term “network” is much more common and less misleading than “communication channel”.<n>You can share files with your neighbors on the street, so the term isn’t just for computers, either.<n><n>Input:What is the area of a circle when its radius is 6 inches?<n>Output: The area of a circle is A=3.1416*r2r2.<n>Since r=6, then A=3.16r2r2=3.14r24r2=.995761r24r2.<n>So A=.9957r24r2 or A=.995r4r4.Round to 2 decimals:<n>A=.995r24r2<n>So the final answer.1335m2=.133m2<n>

His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur. Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input:What kind of driving leads to accidents? ### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input:What is required to be good at playing tennis? ### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input:Where do bees congregate with red flowerS? Choices:  A: trash can B: honey C: bouquet of flowers D: rose garden E: field of flowers<n>Output:		FlowerS in a bouquet of flowers<n>The statement is that they are associated with red flowerS.  This is true of both roses, whose color is red, and of honey, the substance bees make from nectar and pollen.<n>So this is (A or B or C or D or E).<n>(E)is not the right answer, bees do not go to flowerS, that is what they collect pollen and nectar from, not congregateS.<n>(B)is the right answer.<n><n>Input: A certain bacterium reproduces every 3.9 minutes. Write an expression, in terms of the time t, which represents the average number of bacterial divisions occurring before time t. Be sure to distinguish between variables (t, b, and n) and constant (pi) in your expression.<n>Output: n=3.9/pi=<<n=3.9/3.9=1>>1<n>b=3.9*n=<<b=3.9 * 3.9=13.73>>13.73<n>and the final answer n13.73 is 1<n><n>Input: 1-3=<<1-3=2>>2<n>5-4=<<5-4=1>>1<n><n>Output:14 <n><n>Input: The area of rectangular region is A. the width (n) of the region, and the length (k) of the region are both measured in inches. 234 2<n><n>Output:k*n=234=<<k*n=2*34=68>>68<n><n>k=68/n=<<k=68 */3=23>>23<n><n>n*k=2*3=<<2*3=6>>6.<n><n>and the final answer the area=6*2=<<6*2=12>>12<n><n><n><n>
### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input:The city's community garden was demolished for yet another what? Choices:  A: wasteland B: ocean C: desert D: parking lot E: flowers<n>Output:		A: wasteland. <<A: wasteland. >>There were some people who enjoyed digging for old treasures in the ruins of the community garden.  So, the answer is wasteland.<n><n>Given: The bus leaves at 7:05 AM. >> It leaves at 7:10 AM.<n>Output: The bus leaves at $7:10$7:10 AM now. It is 5 minutes later. The bus stops at 7:15 AM to pick up the passengers who are on the last minute. They are <<The bus stops at 7 AM to pick up passengers who are on the very last minute. >> very on the very last minute of passengers are on the very last << They are very on the very last >> minute.<n><n>input:<n>A person can ride a bus for free if he/she is at the bus stop before the bus arrives and gets off after the bus arrives.  How much does person A pay for a round trip if he/she rides the bus from $a$a to $b$b two times?<n>Output: <<Person A needs to pay $4$4.  He rides the bus from A to B two times.  On the same day, he gets off from the bus at A for one time and gets off from the bus. He can do this for free since he is at the last minute of the bus and he gets off from it after the bus arrives at A. He comes back after waiting for 5 minutes at A. So he rides the bus from B to A two times and he gets off after the bus leaves at A. Because of this, he gets off at $b$b and gets on at A. There are two rides from A to B and two rides (from B to $a$a) two times. Thus, there are four rides, $4$4. >><n><n>### Solution：<n><n>The first choice is $30/day$30/day. The first seven days are $190$190. There are $7-1=6$6 days left and they are each $30$30 days. And they add up to be $190$310.<n><n>The second choice is 400/0=20$400/0\rightarrow 20$

### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input:If you want to make a big splash in a river with a rock, from where should you throw it? Choices:  A: mountains countryside B: ground C: bridge D: mountain range E: surface of earth<n>Output:		The ground is the only choice.<n>The river will have the deepest and most stable water directly above the outflow from the river.<n>The ground below the outflow from the ground will allow the greatest distance,<n>and the greatest accuracy, in addition to the least amount of air resistance. (A, C) <n>The lake below ground will not be stable enough to hold any consistent depth. <n>The river, and the ground below the outflow, will be the most consistent places to find stable depths. (E)<n>The river above the outflow from ground has the deepest depth, but it also has the least amount of stable depth below the surface, especially compared to below the outflow from a river. (B, D)<n>The river below the outflow from ground offers a less stable place to throw the rock since it is also at a greater distance of the ground. (B, C, D)<n>The lake below the outflow from of the river will not provide a stable depth. (A, C, D) The rock will always hit the shallower water next to the ground. (A, C D)<n>The mountains countryside on the ground will not be a stable depth to throw from. <n>The river above the ground will give the least amount of depth. <n>The lake below the river will not be a stable place to throw the stone. <n>The land above the river will not be the most stable place to throw.<n><n>
### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input:Where are people likely to find food? Choices:  A: opera B: supermarket C: building D: conference E: apartment<n>Output:		Answer A.<n>Answer B.<n>Answer D.<n>Answer E.<n><n>Input:Two pizzas, one with 8 slices and one with 6, are left over after a party has been eating pizza for an hour. How much pizza was eaten by the party before the leftover pizza arrived?<n>Output:Answer A<n>Answer B<n>Answer D<n>Answer E<n><n>Input:If a train travels 180 mph, how far will it have traveled in 3 hours?<n>Output:480 mph.<n><n><n>Input: A train is travelling 5 times faster than a horse. If the train is travelling 24 miles per hour, how much faster than the horse is it travellling?<n>Output:Answer is it moving 120 miles per hour.
### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. The other is 2*(190) and 4 is 1, so it's only valid because 190 only is valid, for other trips, (day-trip) must be 3, or 4, or 5, or 2 and 1, when (day - 1) is 3, the cost is 0, when (day-1) is 4, and 5, and 2, the cost is still

### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input:He had done a great job with the scary decorations, they were completely what? ### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input:What is likely to have more than one level in a city? How far, in miles, from the end of the freight train is the police car at this instant <n>Output: The police car will over take the end of the freights train (5000/60)+1/2 - 5050/12 -1351/2 + 1/2=<<5000/2 +1/2 -1350>>1850 miles. ### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. Sex and rowing are both temporary in nature, so they are incorrect.<n>Furthermore, dancing doesn't last a lifetime; it has an end or limit, so dancing is incorrect. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input:What is the hope of playing sports without competition? Choices:  A: running B: have fun C: balls touch D: winning E: get tired<n>Output:		The answer is C. If anyone says "B" he does not understand the meaning of playing sports. "B" means, you only have fun, the purpose of it is only fun. In "C", the ball has to touch other guys but in "D", you have to win the game against another team. The only hope of playing sports is only in "C", you have to try to win as possible.<n><n><n><div class="question" align="left"> <n>  <a name="01"></a></div><n><div class="inputs" align="left">  <n><n><n><div id="A" style="color: #C0392B">     <n> <label for="A" class="correct">A. </label> 11<n> <input id="A" name="A" type="radio" value="11" checked="checked">    <n></div><n><div style="display:none">A. 11</div><n><n><n><div  id="B" style="color:  #CC7020"> <n> <label for="B" class="correct">B. </label> 20<n> <input id="B" name="B" type="radio"value="20" >  <n></div><n><n><div  style="display:none"></div>B. 20</div><n><n>  <n><div id="C" style="color: Green"></div><label for="C" class="correct">C. </label> 31<n>        <input id="C"    name="C" type="radio"    value="31"><n>        </div>     <n><n><n><div   id="D" style="color:   #FF5722">  <n>  <label for="D" class="correct">D. </label> 41<n>  <input id="D" name="D" type="radio"  value="41">                 <n><n></div><n></div><n>    <div id="E" style="color: Orange"></div><label for="" class="correct"></label><n>  E. 51                 <n><input   id="E"     name="E" type="radio" /><n></div> <n></div><n>  <div class="feedback clear
### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur. Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input:Sarah wanted to by a new rug. ### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input:What does a chef do when working in the evening? Which two lines are skipped when this program is run? A: 1 B: 2 C: END D: 4 E: 3<n>Output: END is the marker that signals that the entire program has completed. If End is reached, then nothing is skipped.<n>

### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input:What do people in the same family often share? Choices:  A: brown hair B: names C: two eyes D: will E: brains<n>Output:		E.<n><n>Input: If you can travel, all year round to your favourite holiday spot, and fly over night, then how many days of the year would you be able to visit your favourite holiday destination?<n>Output: The output has been determined by counting the number of days in a year, which would normally take 12 months/365=<<12 months/385=0.5>>0.5 a week off work per year. (Or 52 working weeks)<n><n>So the final answer = 1/2 x 365 days=<<1/2 x 14 x365 days=219.15 days>>219.165 days<n><n>Input:How many days of the year are there, including leap years? ### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input:James chose to not to print the cards, because he wanted to be more personal. ### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input:What emotion do people expressing themselves show when they trip in front of a crowd and break their leg? The new engine allows for unlimited miles. What is the car’s total mileage after this mechanical addition?<n>Output: The total mileage of a car that has an unknown starting mileage and an additional mechanical addition of unlimited miles equals the starting mileage of the vehicle after the mechanical replacement.<n>Here's what this equation should look like: X+450-1=<<X+0-1>>1+450-450+1=1<n>Therefore after the mechanical addition to the vehicle, X=<<X>>2+450 (the new number of miles).<n><n>Input: Two train tracks parallel each other but run in different directions. Choices:  A: interesting B: fun C: joyful or painful D: very important E: free<n>Output:		Choices A, B, E are incorrect.<n><n>Input: How many different two digit numbers can you make using the numbers 0-4?<n>Output: <n>There are $<<<6!/2!><>>$6!/2! ways of arranging the digits 2 and 0, without repetition, and there are 5 choices for the $<<<<6-2=4>>>>$4 remaining digits.<n>So by choosing two digits from any of the $<<2!>>2!$ possible choices and repeating the same digit, there are $<<2!/1>$2!/1$$$2!/1>$ ways to choose the positions of the digits.<n>Additionally we account for the possibility that the repeated digit is at either the left or the right end position by adding the 2 cases to the previous expression.<n>Thus, the number of possible arrangements is: $2!/1>$ + $0!$ + $2!/1>$$2!/1>$<n>Thus the final answer is $2!/1> + 0 + 2!/1>$$= 5$$= 5<n><n>Input: A friend claims that $0 < a < b < 1$. Therefore if $a + b >2$, then $a + b <1$.<n><n>If $a +b >2$, then either $a >1$ or $b >1$, and in either case, the value of the fraction $a/b$ must be greater than 1, which is false, so the above condition violates the 1st condition that $0 < a$, thus, $a +b > 2$ and $0 < a$, are impossible.<n><n>If $a < b$, then $a - b > 1$, which is false, again because if $a$ and $a - b$ are both less than 1, they cannot be greater than

How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input:In what place could you find air that has been breathed by only a few people recently? Choices:  A: train station B: house C: cupboard D: cricket stadium E: surface of earth<n>Output:		Given all the breathing air is recycled, you need not go anywhere as the place where you are living will have air similar to that you have recently breathed.  Nowhere.
### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input:Where would you find a sign with some people lined up next to it? How many people are total?<n>Output: Choose choice E which is 18 since 7+11 = 18<n><n>Input: How many square inches are there in a square yard?<n>Output: Since 1 foot equals 12 inches, and 12*12 equals 144 square inches, there are 144 square<n>         inches in a square yard.<n><n>Input: How fast will a train traveling at 40 miles an hour travel in hours from point A to point B?<n>Output: Choosing choice  C (half a day).<n><n>Input: How much fuel is needed to power a rocket that travels into space after starting with $320.00?<n>Output: Since the rocket travels 264,000 miles, and traveling 1 mile costs (1/20 of an hour of energy)<n>            25.6 watt hours worth of energy, the energy required to power it can be estimated as:<n>            25.4 * 264,160 = (15,824,640) watt hours (15.8 million watt hours or 15.8 gigwatt hours)(cost for one<n>            15.8 gigawatt hour energy cell = $75) = $1150 - therefore the total cost of the rocket flight is<n>            1150 + 320 = $1470(The actual cost of the flight was $1560 which is close)<n><n><n><n>```python<n># Instruction - Input the question and the answers to the questions into this array and save as an excel sheet<n><n>q_set={}<n><n>q_set['a

Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input:What appliance uses water and soap? ### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input:The whole family was playing cards, they were full of joy and what? Choices:  A: sadness B: happiness C: amusement D: losing money E: anger<n>Output:		C<n>The whole family was losing money<n><n>#!/bin/python<n>"""<n>Python<n>Problem:<n>	18/7<n>	3+3+4+5<n>	3^4<n>	1/0<n>	100/12<n>	25^2<n>5.718*5.98<n>"""<n>import sys<n><n>def main():<n>	sys.stdout.write("Output:")<n>	sys.stdout=open('answers.txt', 'w')<n>	answers = [None] * 6<n><n>	answer = raw_input('Input: ')<n>	answer1=input('Input: ')#instruction to  user<n>	answer2=input('Input:')#instruction to user<n>	answer3=input('Input: ').split()#instruction to user to input answer in different string<n>	for i in range(0, len(answer3)): #loop over answer<n>		answers[i] = answer[i]<n><n>	answers.sort()<n>	count=1#initialize counter<n><n><n>	#for i in range(1, 6):<n>	for i in answers:<n>		if i == 3.0:<n>		    print 3<n>		if i==5.99:<n>		    #print 10<n>		else:<n>		    sys.stdout.write("%f\n" % i)<n><n>		if i!=answers[-1] and answers[-1]!=answers[i-1]:<n>			if i.isdecimal() and answers[-1] > i:<n>				system.stdout.write("A"<n>			else:<n><n>				sys.stdout.writeln("%f" % i)<n>				count+=1<n><n>			if not i.isdecimal():<n>				if answers[-1] >= i:<n>		answer = count<n>		print answer<n>		print ""<n>		<n>if __name__ == "__main__":<n>    main()<n>
### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input:The king was to meet an ambassador, where would the meet? Choices:  A: court B: dinning room C: throne room D: monarchy E: castle<n>Output:		Castle is right<n><n>Input:Choose a day, a month, and a year in which you were born. The first two digits of year gives the number of digits. The last digit gives the number of letters in month. Digitize year if required. Then what's the value of your month? <n>Output:8 month of august
### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input:Where does a person need to get when they have more kids? ### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input:Riding bike through rough terrain can be dangerous, one could find themselves what? If a driver rents a car for 150 miles and drives it at 50 miles per hour, how much will the driver pay for the rental, in dollars?<n>Output: The daily rental at 50 per mile is 50 miles per day/50-mile per day = <<50 miles per day / 50-mile per>> day/50 mile cost= <<day/50 mile cost >>30 cents for the first 150 miles<n>For the next 150 miles at 50 miles cost is 50 miles/0.55 mile =<<50 miles/0/55 mile=<<50 miles/<<<50 miles/<<<<50 miles/71.35<n>Closing the fraction 71.35+30cents=<<71.35 + 30cents=101.35>>101.36.<n>So the final is 101.38<n>
### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input:Where does a spoon go on one side of a plate? Choices:  A: bowl of soup B: serving dish C: table setting D: placemat E: glass of iced tea<n>Output:		The spoon is never on the placemat.  So the only remaining choices are B, C and D.<n>The spoon is never in the bowl of soup because it's too tall and is always put upright to drink.  The spoon is never in a glass of Iced Tea because the  table setting is served on the side of the glass.  The spoon only appears to be on the glass of iced tea because the plate and glass are facing downward.  The spoon never appears on the table setting because it's on a plate and must never touch a flat surface.  Therefore the spoon must be on the placemat or the serving dish, with the placemat being the only place with flat surface.<n>The spoon goes on the plate when it is done serving.  When it is done serving it is put on the placemat but it must never touch a table and so is moved to the serving dish.<n>Since only one object can be on top of another without touching, the placemat wins because the plate will never be completely on top of the placemat.<n><n>Input:A pond is circular with a radius of 7 miles. A bridge is to be constructed so that it reaches all the way around the pond. How much more bridge is required to make the circle an ellipse?<n>Output: If an ellipse were constructed then the  x-coordinate for all points on the ellipse would be different.  A point along the original radius for an ellipse would be x = r cos theta /  r with sin theta.   The sin theta for one point along the original radius is equal to 0 and the others are >0 and < 1.  The ellipse is constructed such that it is centered on the original radius so that r = 7* (r cos (theta)) /  (r sin  theta).  The area outside the ellipse would have to be subtracted from the original circle.   This is 4*pi*r*r = 288.  That is 288/ 7*(7* (r cos theta))/ (r sin theta).  Note that only one factor varies, not both r and r sin theta.  The result should be much more than 1.2.<n><n>Input:Which of the following types of transport

His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input:What does a virus primarily do to a person? Choices: A. 1 kg B.  3 lbs C.100 oz D.900 g<n>Output: D. 900 g<n>Input: A 50-pound box of cereal cost how many dollars at $25 dollars for 25 pounds? Choices: A 50 B 125 C 250 D 25 dollars<n>Output: A<n>Input: A person can jump or 8 miles per hour. For how long can the person maintain this rate of speed? Choices: A minute B 2 minutes C 600 seconds D 30 minutes E 2000 seconds<n>Output: B<n><n>This is a programming problem, so just to clarify how to solve this problem.<n>The first question, The car rental question, we should ask if we will return the car after 4 days. If yes, go back to the first day.<n>And then check the next 3 cases to see how much was the price of the car rental in the different cases.<n><n><img src="./3_CodingTest2(1).JPG" width="800" height="600" /><n><n>The second question:<n>Traveling back to one day at time. Just need to check the different cases and if the answer is correct, then the program works correctly.<n><n><img  src="./3_Hangar(2).JPG" width=800 height=600 /><n><n>### The car rental question can be solved by<n><n>```<n>d = 0;<n>while(d <= 11) {<n>    if(d == 4)<n>        d = 7;<n>    else<n>        d = d+1;<n>    if(d%7 == 0)<n>        car_r_fst(d);<n>    else <n>        car_r(d);<n>}<n>```
### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input:What is a place that might not always have a queen? His state sales tax is 4%.  How much money does he spend during a week?<n>Output: During a week there are 7*7=<<7*7=49>>49 total days.<n>In our calculations, the first $1.89/$2.05/$15.87 is used to buy the cigarettes, coffee, and gas respectively.<n>Then, $1.89/2.05/15.87=<<1.89/1.87=4.3>>4.35.<n>Thus, $4.35/$1.89=<<4.35/$4.35=1>>1.<n>So the total weekly cost is 1$ only.<n><n>Input: A bus takes 100 people to a carnival. Determine the cost of transporting the 100 people in the bus.<n>Output: First we need to decide that there are four type of passenger 1.$6<=$2<=$4 and $2<=$4<=$6<n>Then the total revenue for the bus = $200<n>From that we have 2$/4=<<2$/4=0.5>>5<n>So the first bus has a profit of 5.<n>Then the total amount of people are calculated by summing<n>100+100+18*5<n><n>The number of passenger from 2$ to 4$ are multiplied by 1.5<n><n><n><n>Input: A man pays $3.00 for a gallon of milk, $2.00 for a loaf of bread, and $1.00 for a can of vegetables. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input:What place is not interesting to children? ### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input:People are purposefully harming others, what trait are they exhibiting? Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input:The other passengers on the bus were quite loud, so he put on his headphones to relax and what? ### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input:In the movie a fragile man is causing accidents, his hope is to find a person opposite of him who is what? Given n's value, write boolean expressions that evaluate to true if n is above average, and evaluate to false if n is below average. How many booleans can you write?<n>Output: If n is above average: n>749 or n>926<n>and if n is below average: n<749 or n<926<n>The total below and above average booleans can be expressed via n and x (for x:1)<n>n(n-749)(n-926)=(n(n-x)(n-x))/(x-x)=(n)*/(1-.5)=n*(929-926)-n*(1-929)/(.5)=(n)(.5)(2)*=n(1)=n<n><n><n>

Choices:  A: gy mnasiu m B: motel room C: seashore D: bath room E: locker room<n>Output:		A: gy mnasiu  m<n>B: motel room<n>C: seashore<n>D: bath room<n>E: locker room<n><n>Explanation:  motel is derived from the words  mo (in) telo (inn) and  motel=mo(in) telo(inn)el so  motel=mo  telo el<n><n>Input:Gymnassia<n>Output:gy mnasiu<n>(The letters m and n are pronounced in the same way.  "Gy" represents letters pronounced with a hard G sound.  Greek spellings are quite complicated, and if we wanted this to also work in Spanish, we'd have to deal with "x", "j" and "ch")<n><n>Input: The letters in the word  moist are m, o, i, and s. So if we "spell out" the letters in the word mop, it is M=6 O=15 P=16 and so on.  If we had wanted to spell out the whole words we could have started with M=600 and O=1000. The word moist has 17 letters (m and o have been removed).<n>We can figure the number of letters in the word by doing M = 600 * (17-6) / 15 and getting 1307.<n>The total number of letters in the  whole sentence is 6 letters.  Because the first word in the sentence had four letters and the rest of the  words are of one syllable each, the first word is the only word consisting of four letters.  Therefore, the number of syllables per word  is always (500 - the number of letters in one of the five one-syllable words).  So  if we divide 570 (the 500 - the 3 one-syllable letters of the word moist) by 15,  we come up with 38 which is the number of letters  the first word contains.<n><n>Solution:The number of syllables in this type of sentence is the number of letters minus the number if letters in the first word. As this is <n>the only word with more than 3 letters, this is true. Divide 600 by 15 to get the number of letters

Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input:Lindy was a senior. ### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Choices:  A: hatred B: surprised C: compliments D: dedication E: solutions<n>Output:		A hatred is not what its about, D focus <n><n>Input: the answer is A.  (Its not the only way to answer a problem, but in this case, my answer was correct: A: hatred)<n><n>Input:  What is -5 divided by -8?<n><n>Output: The answer is -.625 or -62.5%<n><n><n>Input: A pizza restaurant offers a family menu which includes 2 medium one-topping pies for $20.  If a slice of pizza costs $2.49, how much will a family of 3 pay at most for a meal that includes 2 slices for each guest?<n><n>Output:  2 medium pizzas are $40 2 pizzas per person is 2*40=<<2*40=80>> $80<n>3 people is 3*80=<<3*80=240>>240<n>Hence, the answer is $240<n><n>Input for answer: $80<n><n>Input: How many square feet are in a room that is 14 ft long and 12 ft wide?<n><n>Output: <n><n>14+12=26<n>14*14=196<n>12*12=144<n><n>Hence, 196+144=<< 196+ 144=340>> 340 square feet<n> <n>Input: What is the average length of a string of DNA in the cell nucleus of a human with 7 feet of height?<n><n>Output: Answer: The average length is 7 feet plus 3 centimeters is 7.2<n>Hence, 7.2/2=<<7.2/2 =3.6>> 3.6 feet of DNA per cell<n><n>Input: A 4ft 10in tall man and a 4ft 12in tall woman visit their 42in wide sofa and find it too small to sit comfortably so they decide to buy a new one.  They find a new sofa that is 6ft long.  Will a sofa that measures 6ft be big enough for the man, but not the woman?<n><n>Output: No, the answer is NO
### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input:What chore might a child have to do after breakfast, before getting on the bus? Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input:If you're traveling along a highway what item made of paper can you use to find your way? Choices:  A: united states B: atlas C: developed land D: park E: countryside<n>Output:		A atlas<n>If you traveling along a highway, you can use an atlas (either paper-based or electronic) to get oriented and find your way.<n><n>Input:A man is hiring a car to drive from Austin to San Antonio. The cost per mile is \$7.07. There are 70 miles from Austin to San Antonio. How much money he will spent driving from Austin to San Antonio?<n>Output: First, he spent \$70.70 to cover the 70 miles. Then he spent \$12(4-70) = \$99.30 extra miles.  So the final answer is $129.30<n>
### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur. Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input:Where in your entrance hall can you keep you head wear? What angle in the corner of the two signs should be in the same place?<n>Output: Either no angle is visible, or the angle is 30 degrees.<n>If he puts the signs in a way that they are parallel with each other but still facing the road, each angle in the corner of each sign will be 30 degrees. Otherwise, both angles are hidden.<n><n>Input:A person purchases 14 shirts for $8. ### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input:If I wanted to see a lizard in its natural habitat but I do not speak Spanish, where would I go? Choices:  A: utah B: south america C: new hampshire D: japan E: new mexico<n>Output:		New Mexico<n>The only place that contains Lizard-in-a natural habitat-Spainish.<n><n><n>Input: You have 5 pieces of fruit, all of the same flavor. There are 2 large and 3 small pieces. There are 10 pieces of fruit in total. You would like to have exactly 5 pieces of fruit.<n>Which of the following is the MINIMUM possible amount of fruit pieces?<n>Output: The solution is an equation, which reads that we can select up to two large fruits, or three small fruits.
